ZCZC EE24
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
FRIDAY TO MONDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND
MARITIME AGENCY AT 152300 UTC
ON FRIDAY EVENING LOW PRESSURE OVER SCANDINAVIA WILL FILL
AND MOV EWARDS AWAY FM THE AREA AS A RIDGE OF HIGH
PRESSURE FM THE AZORES HIGH BEGINS TO BUILD NE ACROSS
WERN SEA AREAS AND THEN MOV EWARDS ACROSS THE UK DURING
SATURDAY AND SUNDAY. AN ATLANTIC LOW WILL MOV NE TO THE S
OF ICELAND BY SATURDAY EVENING REMAINING SLOW MOV
THROUGH SUNDAY AND MONDAY. ON MONDAY THE ANTICYCLONE
ACROSS THE UK WILL SLWY DECLINE EWARDS. OCCASIONAL STRG
MAINLY N TO NW WINDS WILL AFFECT MOST OF NITON ON FRIDAY
EVENING EXCEPT THE EERN ENGLISH CHANNEL. WINDS WILL EASE
ACROSS ALL AREAS FM THE W DURING SATURDAY. OCCASIONAL
STRG SW WINDS ARE LIKELY TO DEVELOP OVER SHANNON FOR A
TIME LATER ON SATURDAY AND AGAIN DURING SUNDAY
EXTENDING TO SOLE NW FITZROY AND FASTNET BY THE EVENING
AND ON MONDAY EXTENDING INTO LUNDY AND IRISH SEA. LATER
ON MONDAY INCR TO NEAR GALE STRENGTH IN NW SHANNON.
